        <para>Before cataloguing a publication inside Tamboti, you need to decide which type of publication it is: 
            </para>
        <ul>
            <li>a book</li>
            <li>an edited volume</li>
            <li>a contribution to an edited volume</li>
            <li>a periodcal</li>
            <li>an article in a periodical</li>
            <li>a book series</li>
        </ul>
        <para>If the publication is written in a script that is not Latin, for instance in Arabic or Chinese, you can transliterate (transcribe, romanise) most of the bibliographical information, and translate
            the title. This action requires more input fields, but it makes the bibliographical entry more useful to others, who may not know the
            language in question. Each of the six publication types therefore come in two variants, one simple and one advanced (with transliteration).</para>
